;s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"Help Local Vendor with Your WordPress Marketplace in This Global Pandemic\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://wedevs.com/299214/local-vendor-for-wordpress-marketplace/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"https://wedevs.com/299214/local-vendor-for-wordpress-marketplace/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 24 Apr 2020 10:44:47 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Dokan\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Tips and Tricks\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"WordPress Marketplace\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://wedevs.com/account/?p=299214\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:629:\"<p>The global pandemic of COVID-19 is on a rampage. People have no way than staying home. The normal transportation is almost off except for emergencies. Eventually, companies are helpless to reduce productions or even put on a halt.&#160; However, people likely to purchase over the internet more than ever. As the brick and mortar stores [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/299214/local-vendor-for-wordpress-marketplace/\">Help Local Vendor with Your WordPress Marketplace in This Global Pandemic</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/account\">weDevs</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"Kaji Enamul Islam\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24923:\"\n<p>The global pandemic of COVID-19 is on a rampage. People have no way than staying home. The normal transportation is almost off except for emergencies. Eventually, companies are helpless to reduce productions or even put on a halt.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, people likely to purchase over the internet more than ever. As the brick and mortar stores remain open for a limited time. Where every industry is suffering, eCommerce may have the slightest chances to prevail.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So you need to be more responsible as a WordPress marketplace owner. Besides, if you are planning to open a <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/123073/before-starting-woocommerce-multi-vendor-store/\">WooCommerce multivendor store</a>, now it is the best time.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this blog, we will show you how to inspire local vendors to sell through your WordPress marketplace, and the easiest way to build one. Keep reading. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"559\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2020/01/How-to-create-a-Used-electronics-store-using-the-SPMV-module-in-Dokan-1-1024x559.png\" alt=\"WooCommerce marketplace\" class=\"wp-image-265195\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/01/How-to-create-a-Used-electronics-store-using-the-SPMV-module-in-Dokan-1-1024x559.png 1024w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/01/How-to-create-a-Used-electronics-store-using-the-SPMV-module-in-Dokan-1-300x164.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/01/How-to-create-a-Used-electronics-store-using-the-SPMV-module-in-Dokan-1-768x420.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/01/How-to-create-a-Used-electronics-store-using-the-SPMV-module-in-Dokan-1-1536x839.png 1536w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/01/How-to-create-a-Used-electronics-store-using-the-SPMV-module-in-Dokan-1-45x25.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/01/How-to-create-a-Used-electronics-store-using-the-SPMV-module-in-Dokan-1-112x61.png 112w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/01/How-to-create-a-Used-electronics-store-using-the-SPMV-module-in-Dokan-1.png 1622w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Why Redesign Your WordPress Marketplace for Local Vendor</h2>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>The performance of the online economy becomes the performance of the retail economy overall. </p><cite>Vivek Pandya, Lead Analyst, Adobe Digital Insights</cite></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>The average sales of daily groceries through online stores is on the rise. Grocery spending accounts for <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-31/americans-adopting-e-commerce-faster-than-ever-amid-pandemic\">8%</a> of total eCommerce now compared to 6% from three years ago. In addition to that, almost every type of product categories impacted by the pandemic. Either more or less. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Take a look at the list below. <a href=\"https://www.visualcapitalist.com/shoppers-buying-online-ecommerce-covid-19/\">VisualCapitalist</a> shared it a few days ago. It shows the top <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/191333/how-to-write-a-profitable-product-description-ultimate-guide/\">eCommerce product</a> categories which saw a huge surge in demands in recent times. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"670\" height=\"370\" src=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Top-product-categories-during-pandemic.png\" alt=\"top product categories for WordPress marketplace\" class=\"wp-image-299237\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Top-product-categories-during-pandemic.png 670w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Top-product-categories-during-pandemic-300x166.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Top-product-categories-during-pandemic-45x25.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Top-product-categories-during-pandemic-112x62.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 670px) 100vw, 670px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>On the contrary, there are a lot of popular products that notice a significant drop. To compare the situation, you should also understand it nontheless.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"821\" height=\"370\" src=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/declining-product-categories-during-the-pandemic-1.png\" alt=\"Declining product categories for WordPress marketplace\" class=\"wp-image-299239\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/declining-product-categories-during-the-pandemic-1.png 821w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/declining-product-categories-during-the-pandemic-1-300x135.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/declining-product-categories-during-the-pandemic-1-768x346.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/declining-product-categories-during-the-pandemic-1-45x20.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/declining-product-categories-during-the-pandemic-1-112x50.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 821px) 100vw, 821px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see, most of the demanding products are easier to <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/blog/191493/best-things-to-sell-online\">sell online</a>. And, people care more for food and sanitization. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In such circumstances, you should look out for local vendors who want to sell their daily products or any kind of household items. Evidently they are is at risk because people can\'t able to go to the market.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You need to redesign the process of your online multivendor store. Make changes to your vendor policy. Be more open and flexible to the people who use your store to sell their items. As well as your consistent vendors, you should focus more on your <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/blog/171322/multi-vendor-shipping-with-dokan\">local sellers and suppliers</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Well let\'s get into the details one by one. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Inspire Referrals for New Vendors to Your WordPress Marketplace</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"559\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2019/09/Referral-Marketing--1024x559.png\" alt=\"Referral-Marketing\" class=\"wp-image-228373\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/09/Referral-Marketing--1024x559.png 1024w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/09/Referral-Marketing--300x164.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/09/Referral-Marketing--768x420.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/09/Referral-Marketing--45x25.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/09/Referral-Marketing--112x61.png 112w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/09/Referral-Marketing-.png 1622w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Birds of a feather flock together. This happens to everyone. Doctors know doctors, writers befriend writers. Therefore, your existing vendors must have known a lot of other vendors. It is our social design.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wedevs.com/104722/customer-support-multi-vendor-marketplace/\">B2B</a> companies with referrals can achieve a <a href=\"https://influitive.com/blog/infographic-17-stats-about-b2b-referrals-you-should-know-but-probably-dont/\">70%</a> higher conversion rate. During this grave time, you should tell your vendors to aware and responsible. Hence initiating a referral program is what you need to do. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>And that\'s the beginning of it. Here\'s what you can do step by step. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Ask your existing vendor to inspire their familiar local vendor to open a shop in your WordPress marketplace. </li><li>Offer referral to every new local vendor they suggest to your multivendor shop.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can check this referral campaign of Sam Club as an example. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"721\" height=\"395\" src=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/referral-club.png\" alt=\"referral vendors\" class=\"wp-image-299279\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/referral-club.png 721w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/referral-club-300x164.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/referral-club-45x25.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/referral-club-112x61.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 721px) 100vw, 721px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Whenever any of your existing vendors make a referral, they will get incentives. Once someone opens a shop, he can suggest a new vendor to keep the cycle going on.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Offer Extra Benefits to Local Vendors</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"811\" height=\"443\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2017/07/4th-july-wordpress-discounts-offers.png\" alt=\"WordPress Discount Offers\" class=\"wp-image-90532\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2017/07/4th-july-wordpress-discounts-offers.png 811w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2017/07/4th-july-wordpress-discounts-offers-300x164.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2017/07/4th-july-wordpress-discounts-offers-768x420.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2017/07/4th-july-wordpress-discounts-offers-600x328.png 600w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2017/07/4th-july-wordpress-discounts-offers-750x410.png 750w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2017/07/4th-july-wordpress-discounts-offers-810x443.png 810w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 811px) 100vw, 811px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Vendors who are accustomed to the brick and mortar facing hardship. They have to shut their physical shop down most part of the day. So when you all set to run a <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/86500/customer-relationship-for-ecommerce/\">referral program</a> keep yourself ready for a new policy. Maybe they have options to go for several multivendor. Maybe they haven\'t. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Count it as a social awake. Set new benefits for any local vendor who wants to open a shop in your WordPress marketplace. Try to be competitive. Don\'t lower your rate too much. Neither asking for a high rate. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Aside from the <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/blog/232788/introducing-combine-commission-rate-on-dokan\">commission rate</a>, it\'s a good idea to offer extra benefits.  For example, you can allow any new local vendors to sell their first product without taking any commission. Or offer them a free social marketing campaign for a specific time. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Social Media Campaign for Your WordPress Marketplace</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wedevs.com/104846/reshaping-content-marketing-strategy/\">Marketing campaigns</a> are always the most effective path to gain attention. The good news is you have a lot of medium to spread your news. There was a time when local newspapers were a thing everyone reading or sneaking out for advertisements. But now you have social media, videos, and blogs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>According to <a href=\"https://www.smartinsights.com/social-media-marketing/social-media-strategy/new-global-social-media-research/\">Smart Insights</a>, people around the world spending an average of 2.24 hours a day on social media. If you lower the head-counts, the percentage will be higher. Thus you have an immense opportunity to reach your news through these platforms. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It\'s the ultimate tool to keep people awake with your offers and updates. For example, Amazon often uses Pinterest to share its self-produced or <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/docs/dokan/vendor-dashboard/products/\">vendors product</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"757\" height=\"409\" src=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/social-media-ads.png\" alt=\"social campaign for local vendor\" class=\"wp-image-299291\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/social-media-ads.png 757w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/social-media-ads-300x162.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/social-media-ads-45x24.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/social-media-ads-112x61.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 757px) 100vw, 757px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>To inspire local vendors, you can feature your existing ones. Try to focus on how they making profits during this pandemic. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Furthermore, they are comparatively cost-effective. You can run <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/93930/social-media-growth-hacks-startups/\">social media ads</a> highly targeted for a local audience. Create brand videos and share them through your Facebook or Twitter page, Instagram, and YouTube channel. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Email Campaign Centered on Pandemic</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"811\" height=\"443\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2019/09/Email-marketing-for-sales-growth.png\" alt=\"Email-marketing-for-wordpress-marketplace\" class=\"wp-image-228371\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/09/Email-marketing-for-sales-growth.png 811w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/09/Email-marketing-for-sales-growth-300x164.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/09/Email-marketing-for-sales-growth-768x420.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/09/Email-marketing-for-sales-growth-45x25.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/09/Email-marketing-for-sales-growth-112x61.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 811px) 100vw, 811px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Sending marketing emails to your local vendors is one of the effective ways to help them with your WordPress marketplace. You should know that <a href=\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/911592/frequency-consumers-checking-work-emails-outside-work-hours/\">82%</a> of workers check their emails regardless of their business hours. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your campaign should be focused on the solution during this pandemic. Before you begin, <a href=\"https://getwemail.io/how-to-build-an-email-list-with-wemail/\">lead generation</a> has the utmost importance. There are two considerations here. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://happyaddons.com/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"90\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2019/11/HappyAddons.png\" alt=\"Happy Elementor addons\" class=\"wp-image-247654\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/11/HappyAddons.png 970w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/11/HappyAddons-300x28.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/11/HappyAddons-768x71.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/11/HappyAddons-45x4.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2019/11/HappyAddons-112x10.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 970px) 100vw, 970px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>One,  you can not send emails to random people. Try to find out the email address of your local vendors. Either through your business development team or by making any local search. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Two, never send emails to inactive addresses. It is fruitless to any sense. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some tips you may follow while creating your email campaign. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Try to show empathy towards your local vendors. </li><li>Hints them how your multivendor WooCommerce store going to help them. </li><li>Add helpful content link that guides them to the easiest way to your WordPress marketplace</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>After you have a strong email list, you should <a href=\"https://getwemail.io/how-to-warm-up-a-brand-new-domain-for-sending-emails/\">warm up a brand new domain</a> for your new outreach. You need to sound like a professional. Show the intention of being a real help.  Therefore, using a robust <a href=\"https://getwemail.io/\">email marketing service</a> would be a great enforcer to your success. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Organize Virtual Events for Your WordPress Marketplace</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"559\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2020/04/How-we-are-using-WP-ERP-to-manage-remote-team-1-1024x559.png\" alt=\"managing teams remotely for WordPress marketplace\" class=\"wp-image-298942\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/How-we-are-using-WP-ERP-to-manage-remote-team-1-1024x559.png 1024w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/How-we-are-using-WP-ERP-to-manage-remote-team-1-300x164.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/How-we-are-using-WP-ERP-to-manage-remote-team-1-768x420.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/How-we-are-using-WP-ERP-to-manage-remote-team-1-1536x839.png 1536w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/How-we-are-using-WP-ERP-to-manage-remote-team-1-45x25.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/How-we-are-using-WP-ERP-to-manage-remote-team-1-112x61.png 112w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/How-we-are-using-WP-ERP-to-manage-remote-team-1.png 1622w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Trade shows and conferences are one of the top places where marketplace owners can source vendors. But the <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/287707/wedevs-status-update-amid-the-covid-19-outbreak/\">corona outbreak</a> and global pandemic make it impossible to arrange or attend such physical marketing programs. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, it\'s become easier to arrange online events. To cope up with the current situation, virtual events are on growing popularity. Anyway, it is on the rise since the last few years. People are more likely to join remote video conferences. According to Cisco, videos will account for <a href=\"https://livestream.com/blog/62-must-know-stats-live-video-streaming\">82%</a> of internet traffic by 2022. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, as a <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/152862/customize-marketplace-with-dokans-free-extensions/\">WordPress marketplace</a> owner, you can throw such video campaigns and conferences. Before you start, you can consider the tips we are mentioning now. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Create blogs and video content to announce that you are going to arrange a conference for local vendors. </li><li>Be entertaining. Include quizzes and offer prizes or gifts to the participants. </li><li>Design some courses that can help the vendors. Let them know if they join the events, they will get it for free. </li><li>Spread your news through news portals and other marketing channels. </li><li>Share your announcement blogs and videos through social media. </li><li>Send emails to the respective local vendors and invite them to participate. </li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Well, there are lot of methods to organize virtual events. The easiest way right now is social media live streaming. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can host your program via Facebook live. It will be easier for your local vendor to join your live directly by commenting. You can take questions, and answer any queries instantly. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another way is hosting the virtual event through YouTube live. It is also free if your channel has 100+ subscribers. Then it must be verified with an active phone number. In case your channel is new, it\'s a better option to host live through any established <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/233430/ultimate-youtube-marketing-strategy-for-smes-how-to-make-it-worth-doing/\">YouTube channel</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Making Phone Calls Not Dead Yet</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"960\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2020/04/telemarketing-for-wordpress-marketplace.jpg\" alt=\"telemarketing for wordpress marketplace\" class=\"wp-image-299368\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/telemarketing-for-wordpress-marketplace.jpg 960w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/telemarketing-for-wordpress-marketplace-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/telemarketing-for-wordpress-marketplace-768x512.jpg 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/telemarketing-for-wordpress-marketplace-45x30.jpg 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/telemarketing-for-wordpress-marketplace-112x75.jpg 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Well, a lot of people may think to reach out through phone calls isn\'t effective anymore. Hence, when we are stuck at home like any other pandemic of the past generations, it resembles the same thing. We are a bit going backward. Moreover, most of your local vendors may not have websites. Or they use only phone numbers and email to keep a connection. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can follow the below steps before starting your telemarketing approach. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Make a guideline for these marketing calls. </li><li>Try to be precise and to the point. </li><li>Explain that you want to help in case they are in trouble of selling from their physical shop. </li><li>Be focused on your motive. And, don\'t be too long. </li><li>Follow-up the calls if you get a positive first impression. </li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, gathering phone numbers isn\'t that a hard task. Take an online directory and list the numbers according to your plan. Also you can ask your existing vendors to provide details to the fellow local vendors for support. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Building a Multivendor WordPress Marketplace with Dokan</h2>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>Businesses designed with cloud computing will be the most strong ones in the post-pandemic economy. </p><cite>World Economic Forum</cite></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>To sustain through this harsh time, it\'s a wise decision to <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/296137/build-marketplace-in-wordpress/\">build a multi-vendor WordPress marketplace</a>. WordPress is the largest CMS platform. It is making the process easier for eCommerce with WooCommerce support. Hence, building a WooCommerce multivendor store is super easy with <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/dokan/?utm_source=blog&utm_medium=CTA&utm_content=WordPress+marketplace&utm_campaign=28\">Dokan</a> multivendor eCommerce solution.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you start now, it will need considerably less investment compared to any brick and mortar marketplace. Therefore, you can manage everything including payments over the internet.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, you need three things to create a Multivendor WordPress marketplace. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://wedevs.com/102674/build-wordpress-website-cost/\">Build a WordPress website</a>.</li><li>Integrate Your Site with WooCommerce Plugin </li><li>Integrate Dokan to turn your online store into a multivendor shop</li><li>A suitable WordPress theme</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>It\'s that simple. You can follow the step by step process with this guide here on <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/?p=299214&preview=true&_thumbnail_id=299250\">how to build a multivendor marketplace with Dokan</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"811\" height=\"443\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2020/01/Dokan.png\" alt=\"Dokan to build WordPress Marketplace\" class=\"wp-image-264745\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/01/Dokan.png 811w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/01/Dokan-300x164.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/01/Dokan-768x420.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/01/Dokan-45x25.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/01/Dokan-112x61.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 811px) 100vw, 811px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Get Ready Your Marketplace with Dokan</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We are already facing the toughest time in recent human history. Never before our generations have seen such a global pandemic. So it\'s time to evoke and spread empathy. Help each other to stand up. Every industry is trying to rely on digital platforms. Managing their work by using <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/wp-project-manager-pro/?utm_source=blog&utm_medium=CTA&utm_content=WordPress+marketplace&utm_campaign=28\">remote management tools</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, when you are already earning your living through eCommerce, it\'s high time you should help other people by sharing insights and supports. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>A WordPress marketplace can be a great solution to your local vendors. Try all the way to connect them all with your business. It\'s very usual if you are going to build a new <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/blog/276382/create-baby-products-online-marketplace-with-dokan\">multivendor marketplace</a> right now. In both cases, we believe our tips will guide you to a profitable shore. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So tell us about yourself. Do you have some different suggestions? </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons aligncenter\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-text-color has-background\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/dokan/pricing?utm_source=blog&utm_medium=CTA&utm_content=WordPress+marketplace&utm_campaign=28\" style=\"background-color:#dd3f23;color:#f2e7e7\">Install Dokan & Build Your Multivendor Marketplace Now</a></div>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/299214/local-vendor-for-wordpress-marketplace/\">Help Local Vendor with Your WordPress Marketplace in This Global Pandemic</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/account\">weDevs</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:78:\"https://wedevs.com/account/299214/local-vendor-for-wordpress-marketplace/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"How to use ‘Export-Import, Product duplicator, Single Product Multivendor’ Modules of Dokan\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"https://wedevs.com/298677/how-to-use-dokan-modules/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://wedevs.com/298677/how-to-use-dokan-modules/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 23 Apr 2020 05:00:51 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Dokan\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"how to use dokan modules\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://wedevs.com/account/?p=298677\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:663:\"<p>93% of WordPress online stores are using WooCommerce right now. Hence, more than 30000+ of active WooCommerce multivendor stores are using Dokan. It is evident, Dokan is one of the most popular multivendor eCommerce solutions today. In addition to the powerful features, the credibility of this immense repute goes for Dokan modules. Previously called as [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/298677/how-to-use-dokan-modules/\">How to use &#8216;Export-Import, Product duplicator, Single Product Multivendor&#8217; Modules of Dokan</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/account\">weDevs</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"Kaji Enamul Islam\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27978:\"\n<p><a href=\"https://websitebuilder.org/woocommerce-stats/\">93%</a> of WordPress online stores are using WooCommerce right now. Hence, more than 30000+ of active WooCommerce multivendor stores are using Dokan. It is evident, Dokan is one of the most popular multivendor eCommerce solutions today. In addition to the powerful features, the credibility of this immense repute goes for Dokan modules. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Previously called as add-ons, a bunch of these modules can turn your multivendor WooCommerce shop into a powerhouse. Both for you and your vendors alike. It\'s much like you add an extra hand to your process to accomplish more. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Today we will show you how to use three of such highly resourceful <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/dokan/modules\">Dokan modules</a>. They are Export-Import, Product Duplicator, and Single Product Multivendor. Let\'s follow-through. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Export-Import-Product-duplicator-Single-Product-Multivendor-dokan-modules-2-1024x559.png\" alt=\"how to use dokan modules\" class=\"wp-image-298919\"/></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Export-Import Dokan Modules For Easy Data Transfer</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Enabling your <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/blog/148341/how-to-build-a-multi-vendor-ecommerce-website-dokan-wp-page-builder\">multivendor site</a> with an easy export-import feature is crucial. It allows your vendors to transfer product information with full details anytime they want. This module turns that trait in your store. Vendors can import their data from another online store at ease through .csv or .xml files. Also, they can export the data following the same process.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before you start using <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/dokan/modules/export-import/?utm_source=Blog&utm_medium=landing+page&utm_content=dokan+modules&utm_campaign=28\">Export-import modules</a> of Dokan, you need to activate it from the WordPress dashboard. If you are new to Dokan, you can easily check your configuration either they are alright or not. Just take a closer look at this complete <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/docs/dokan/getting-started/installation-2/\">installation guide</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now keep reading the step by step process to use Export-Import dokan modules. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Step 1. Activate the Dokan Module From Your Dashboard</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The activation process is quite easy. Just go to your WP dashboard. Click on modules on the sidebar. Then you will be directed to this dokan module page below. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"767\" height=\"344\" src=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/export-import-module-dashboard.png\" alt=\"export import module dashboard\" class=\"wp-image-298748\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/export-import-module-dashboard.png 767w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/export-import-module-dashboard-300x135.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/export-import-module-dashboard-45x20.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/export-import-module-dashboard-112x50.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 100vw, 767px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now turn the slide on and thats it for the beginning. You have just allowed your vendors to export-import data from their vendor dashboard. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Step 2. Import Data Into a Vendor Account</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In this step, you need to check if the module is functioning properly. To do this, just log in to a vendor\'s account. As a marketplace owner, you can easily add a demo vendor account from the backend. However, you can check this <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/docs/dokan/all-vendors/adding-new-vendor-from-the-admin-backend/\">guide to add new vendors</a> anytime you want. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>After log in to the vendor dashboard, you will see the &#8216;Tools\' option in the left sidebar. Click on it. Then click on Import. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This module of dokan supports two formats. Therefore, you can import your product information either using .csv or.xml file. Hence, we will show you both of them. </p>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Importing an .xml File</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Let\'s go for the .xml format first. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"776\" height=\"356\" src=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Import-from-Dokan.png\" alt=\"try export import dokan module\" class=\"wp-image-298836\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Import-from-Dokan.png 776w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Import-from-Dokan-300x138.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Import-from-Dokan-768x352.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Import-from-Dokan-45x21.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Import-from-Dokan-112x51.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 776px) 100vw, 776px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>To upload a .xml file, just click on the browse option, choose the file from your computer. Then click import. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>After you\'ve done importing the .csv file, the page will look like this- </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"776\" height=\"355\" src=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/after-Import-csv-.png\" alt=\"import xml at ease\" class=\"wp-image-298851\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/after-Import-csv-.png 776w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/after-Import-csv--300x137.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/after-Import-csv--768x351.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/after-Import-csv--45x21.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/after-Import-csv--112x51.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 776px) 100vw, 776px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now the .xml file you upload will restore the information on your website within few moments. Hence, if you want to upload image files of the respective product, you have to do it manually in the /wp-content/uploads folder.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, importing a CSV file is a bit longer process than the XML format. But don\'t worry, it\'s also an easier one. </p>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Importing a CSV File </strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Stay on the same &#8220;Tools&#8221; page. Click on the Import CSV just below the first option. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"777\" height=\"337\" src=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/import-csv-file-one.png\" alt=\"csv import with export import dokan modules\" class=\"wp-image-298856\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/import-csv-file-one.png 777w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/import-csv-file-one-300x130.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/import-csv-file-one-768x333.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/import-csv-file-one-45x20.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/import-csv-file-one-112x49.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 777px) 100vw, 777px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now click &#8220;Browse&#8221; option. Then upload your CSV file, go for &#8220;Continue button. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"767\" height=\"354\" src=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/import-CSV-file-two.png\" alt=\"import csv with export import dokan modules\" class=\"wp-image-298859\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/import-CSV-file-two.png 767w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/import-CSV-file-two-300x138.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/import-CSV-file-two-45x21.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/import-CSV-file-two-112x52.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 100vw, 767px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>It take a few seconds, or minutes depending on the size of your file. Therefore, you must map columns to complete the importing process. Mapping ensures that your product restored in the expected fields like name, publishing status, availability, or descriptions, etc. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"617\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2020/04/Import-product-xml-map-617x1024.png\" alt=\"Import product xml map columns\" class=\"wp-image-298920\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Import-product-xml-map-617x1024.png 617w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Import-product-xml-map-181x300.png 181w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Import-product-xml-map-768x1274.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Import-product-xml-map-27x45.png 27w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Import-product-xml-map-67x112.png 67w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Import-product-xml-map-300x498.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Import-product-xml-map.png 913w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 617px) 100vw, 617px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>After done mapping, you only need to click &#8220;run the importer&#8221; button at the bottom. On the next page, you can see how your product data restored in your online store by clicking &#8220;View Products&#8221;. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"982\" height=\"499\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-import-csv-4.png\" alt=\"dokan import csv 4\" class=\"wp-image-115471\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-import-csv-4.png 982w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-import-csv-4-300x152.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-import-csv-4-768x390.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 982px) 100vw, 982px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, it\'s that simple if you think even as a vendors point of view. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Step 3. Exporting Data with the Dokan Modules</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Exporting data help your vendors to extract their detailed product info from one of their Dokan account. And upload them to an another account. This is very helpful for your user who are comfortable to doing business through several multivendor. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>From a vendor\'s perspective, you can export data by using CSV and XML format the same as the importing process.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here\'s what you need to do- </p>\n\n\n\n<p>From the same &#8220;Tools&#8221; page in the vendor\'s dashboard, click the &#8220;Export&#8221; button. You may choose from three different options shown in the screenshots below. Usually, when you select this option, your export file will be in an XML format. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"832\" height=\"482\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-export-as-xml.png\" alt=\"dokan export as xml\" class=\"wp-image-115455\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-export-as-xml.png 832w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-export-as-xml-300x174.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-export-as-xml-768x445.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 832px) 100vw, 832px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore,  when you download the XML file, save it as a backup. In case you lost your product data, this file would be a great help nonetheless. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the other hand, if you need to export the data in CSV format, do the following. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"830\" height=\"446\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-export-csv.png\" alt=\"export xml\" class=\"wp-image-115450\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-export-csv.png 830w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-export-csv-300x161.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-export-csv-768x413.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 830px) 100vw, 830px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>After you click on the Export CSV, you will be redirected to the page below. On this page you must define the columns and product types you want to export. It\'s simple. Just make sure that you put the right names. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"565\" height=\"429\" src=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/export-csv-generate-page.png\" alt=\"generate csv to export\" class=\"wp-image-298865\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/export-csv-generate-page.png 565w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/export-csv-generate-page-300x228.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/export-csv-generate-page-45x34.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/export-csv-generate-page-112x85.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 565px) 100vw, 565px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the &#8220;Generate CSV&#8221; button. And you will get the exported product info in a CSV file instantly. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Moreover, there is also a direct approach of using Export-Import Dokan modules. Look at the image below. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1014\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-products-import-export-buttons.png\" alt=\"dokan products import export buttons\" class=\"wp-image-115475\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-products-import-export-buttons.png 1014w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-products-import-export-buttons-300x178.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2014/09/dokan-products-import-export-buttons-768x454.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1014px) 100vw, 1014px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Your vendors can use their product tab in their dashboard to do the job also. However, both option takes you to the export-import page directly. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Well, now we will get a hand to the Product Duplicator. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>How to Use  Product Duplicator Dokan Modules</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"716\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2020/04/Dokan-Duplicate-Product.jpg\" alt=\"Dokan Product Duplicator \" class=\"wp-image-298921\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Dokan-Duplicate-Product.jpg 716w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Dokan-Duplicate-Product-300x201.jpg 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Dokan-Duplicate-Product-45x30.jpg 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/Dokan-Duplicate-Product-112x75.jpg 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 716px) 100vw, 716px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Suppose one of your vendor like to sell a similar product following another vendor. In such cases, he needs to copy the name and description, download the images, and then manually include the product to his/her store. It\'s indeed a hassle. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Product Duplicator just makes your vendor smarter in that case. It helps a vendor to copy a similar product item from one Dokan based online store to another within a single click. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The top advantage of this Dokan modules are- </p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>It enables an &#8220;Add to My Store&#8221; button to every vendor\'s store</li><li>Vendors can sell each other\'s product anytime they feel solidarity</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Well, now check the way to use it in the simples way. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Just Go to your WordPress dashboard. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Go to the &#8220;Plugins&#8221; section. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Search for &#8220;Product Duplicator&#8221; Dokan module. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"415\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2015/06/Dokan-Product-Duplicator-1024x415.png\" alt=\"Dokan Product Duplicator\" class=\"wp-image-104300\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2015/06/Dokan-Product-Duplicator-1024x415.png 1024w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2015/06/Dokan-Product-Duplicator-300x122.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2015/06/Dokan-Product-Duplicator-768x311.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2015/06/Dokan-Product-Duplicator-600x243.png 600w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2015/06/Dokan-Product-Duplicator.png 1359w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Install it in your store and activate the module. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>After the activation, you only need to configure it a bit. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Take a look at the screenshot, change the duplicate button text like &#8220;Add to My Store&#8221;. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"599\" height=\"238\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2018/01/dokan-product-duplicator-settings.png\" alt=\"dokan-product-duplicator-settings\" class=\"wp-image-109345\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2018/01/dokan-product-duplicator-settings.png 599w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2018/01/dokan-product-duplicator-settings-300x119.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 599px) 100vw, 599px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You can do this simply by going to Dokan from your WP-Admin sidebar, then Settings, and then Selling Settings.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"848\" height=\"404\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2018/12/dokan-product-duplicator.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-152936\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2018/12/dokan-product-duplicator.png 848w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2018/12/dokan-product-duplicator-300x143.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2018/12/dokan-product-duplicator-768x366.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 848px) 100vw, 848px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like the image above, your vendor will get a &#8220;Add to My Store&#8221; button whenever they look for a product of any vendors in your multivendor store. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Translating Text Domain by Using Simple Code</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Hence, there is one simple note for you in case you want to translate the text-domain. The method is lucid anyway. It only requires some coding.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 1. Rename the .mo file following this format:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">pluginname-languagecode_countrycode.mo</pre>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 2. Rename the .po file according the below format: </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">dokan-duplicate-product-languagecode_countrycode.po/mo</pre>\n\n\n\n<p>Suppose, you want to translate the text domain into french, the code will look like this &#8211; </p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">dokan-duplicate-fr_FR.mo</pre>\n\n\n\n<p>Furthermore, if you need complete translation help, you can always follow this <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/docs/dokan/common-questions/translate-dokan-plugin/\">guideline to translate Dokan</a> plugins. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Single Product Multivendor to Sell Across the Stores</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>It\'s almost similar to duplicating a product. Therefore, it is a more advanced and <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/dokan/features\">progressive feature</a> you can enable in your multivendor shop. After you install the Single Product Multivendor Dokan Module, your vendors can sell any products they like from other vendor\'s stores. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>That means, your vendors can sell each other\'s products anytime they want. They can use the exact info or customize it, even offer a similar, higher and lower price. So that the customers get a more flexible way to purchase by comparing different prices.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now follow the steps below to know how to use the module and enhanced the features of your Dokan multivendor WooCommerce shop. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Step 1. Change Settings After the Installation</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The installation process is similar to any other plugins or modules we\'ve already shown above. After that stage, you get to change some configurations. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Go to your <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/docs/dokan/dokan-dashboard/admin-dashboard/\">WP-Admin panel</a>, then click on &#8220;Dokan&#8221; and then &#8220;Single Product Multivendor&#8221; just like the image below. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"775\" height=\"425\" src=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/single-product-multivendor-configuration-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-298884\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/single-product-multivendor-configuration-1.png 775w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/single-product-multivendor-configuration-1-300x165.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/single-product-multivendor-configuration-1-768x421.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/single-product-multivendor-configuration-1-45x25.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/single-product-multivendor-configuration-1-112x61.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Mark the box to enable &#8220;Single Product Multiple Vendor&#8221; functionality. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then just below it, you can change the button text. Here we have put it like &#8220;Sell This Item&#8221;. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click Save Changes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now all of your vendor will see the &#8220;Sell This Item&#8221; button whenever they visit any product page. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"891\" height=\"567\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2018/04/dokan-single-product-multivendor-button-text.png\" alt=\"dokan-single-product-multivendor-button-text\" class=\"wp-image-123405\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2018/04/dokan-single-product-multivendor-button-text.png 891w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2018/04/dokan-single-product-multivendor-button-text-300x191.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2018/04/dokan-single-product-multivendor-button-text-768x489.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 891px) 100vw, 891px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, you can set the option to show other vendors selling a similar item. Your vendors or customers will see those items from other sellers just below every added item. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"733\" height=\"368\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2020/04/buy-from-other-vendors.png\" alt=\"buy-from-other-vendors\" class=\"wp-image-298892\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/buy-from-other-vendors.png 733w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/buy-from-other-vendors-300x151.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/buy-from-other-vendors-45x23.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/buy-from-other-vendors-112x56.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 733px) 100vw, 733px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>If you choose this option, you can customize the name anything you like. In the product page, your vendors and customers will see the product like this image below. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"613\" height=\"624\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2017/12/dokan-single-product-multivendor-vendor-list-button.png\" alt=\"dokan single product multivendor vendor list button\" class=\"wp-image-106877\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2017/12/dokan-single-product-multivendor-vendor-list-button.png 613w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2017/12/dokan-single-product-multivendor-vendor-list-button-295x300.png 295w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2017/12/dokan-single-product-multivendor-vendor-list-button-600x611.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 613px) 100vw, 613px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>So, with each changes you made, your vendors will get the updated results. Some of the other options you may like to customize with this Dokan modules are- </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Fixing the position of the other seller\'s product. Your vendors can set it above or below their items. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"780\" height=\"347\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2020/04/above-single-product-tabs.png\" alt=\"above single product tabs\" class=\"wp-image-298896\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/above-single-product-tabs.png 780w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/above-single-product-tabs-300x133.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/above-single-product-tabs-768x342.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/above-single-product-tabs-45x20.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/above-single-product-tabs-112x50.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides that, your vendor also change the product description, vendors info, and add reviews. It is open for more customization. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Step 2. Adding Product from Store-End</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>After you have done all the configuration and save the changes, go to any product from a demo vendor account. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"765\" height=\"418\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2020/04/store-end-view-one.png\" alt=\"store end view one\" class=\"wp-image-298897\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/store-end-view-one.png 765w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/store-end-view-one-300x164.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/store-end-view-one-45x25.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/store-end-view-one-112x61.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 765px) 100vw, 765px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click to &#8220;Sell This Item&#8221;. That\'s all you need to do to add the product in your store. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, the only thing left for you to do the easy updates if you want to change anything. Similar to the screenshot here- </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"764\" height=\"405\" src=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/edit-product-with-dokan-modules.png\" alt=\"edit product with single product multivendor dokan module \" class=\"wp-image-298898\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/edit-product-with-dokan-modules.png 764w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/edit-product-with-dokan-modules-300x159.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/edit-product-with-dokan-modules-45x24.png 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2020/04/edit-product-with-dokan-modules-112x59.png 112w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 764px) 100vw, 764px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Isn\'t that so simple and fun at the same time? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, if you want a more detailed process, you can check this <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/docs/dokan/modules/single-product-multiple-vendor/\">Single Product Multivendor Installation</a> guide. It will show you everything with all the necessary updates regarding the settings. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Final Thoughts On Using Dokan Modules</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You can start using <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/dokan/\">Dokan</a> absolutely free. Moreover, the Product Duplicator Module is available to any version. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But if you want to integrate the Export-Import module, it needs a Business and Enterprise plan. The Single Product Multivendor also available in these two versions including the professional plan. To learn more, you can always check-in for <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/dokan/pricing?utm_source=Blog&utm_medium=landing+page&utm_content=dokan+modules&utm_campaign=28\">Dokan Pricing</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, to enhance your influence and overall eCommerce business, there\'s nothing better than getting a pro version of this robust multivendor WooCommerce store builder. It\'s because the pro-plan includes almost all the superb modules to extend the features of your multivendor marketplace. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So tell us, which Dokan modules seems more important to you? </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons aligncenter\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-background\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/dokan?utm_source=Blog&utm_medium=CTA&utm_content=dokan+modules&utm_campaign=28&ref=1109\" style=\"background-color:#ee9a5e\">Try Dokan Right Now</a></div>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/298677/how-to-use-dokan-modules/\">How to use &#8216;Export-Import, Product duplicator, Single Product Multivendor&#8217; Modules of Dokan</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/account\">weDevs</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"https://wedevs.com/account/298677/how-to-use-dokan-modules/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"Book Products, Events &amp; Hotels, Anything with Dokan WC Booking Module!\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"https://wedevs.com/80622/can-now-book-products-events-hotels-anything-new-dokan-add/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"https://wedevs.com/80622/can-now-book-products-events-hotels-anything-new-dokan-add/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 02 Mar 2020 11:10:07 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Add-on News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Dokan\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Bookings\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"new feature\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://wedevs.com/?p=80622\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:644:\"<p>Dokan WC Booking add-on opens up a whole new possibility for a variety of new products and vendors on your market. Also, this means even markets based on booking products can now emerge. The module is designed especially for hotel booking, conference booking, concerts and all sorts of other services where you need your customers [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/80622/can-now-book-products-events-hotels-anything-new-dokan-add/\">Book Products, Events &#038; Hotels, Anything with Dokan WC Booking Module!</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/account\">weDevs</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Ranan Rahim\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12621:\"\n<p><a href=\"https://wedevs.com/dokan/extensions/woocommerce-booking-integration/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">Dokan WC Booking</a> add-on opens up a whole new possibility for a variety of new products and vendors on your market. Also, this means even markets based on booking products can now emerge.</p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>The module is designed especially for hotel booking, conference booking, concerts and all sorts of other services where you need your customers to book products. </p></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>Any vendor can create bookable and regular or variable products side by side. You can create a site like <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/blog/254769/create-an-airbnb-alternative-site-in-wordpress-with-dokan\">Airbnb</a> using this module. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2016/07/Dokan-Bookings.png\" alt=\"Dokan WC Booking\"/></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>The Dokan WC booking module has excellent customization capabilities. The main focus of this module is to make the options of the WooCommerce Booking module easy to navigate. We are actually bringing all the features from the WooCommerce booking add-on to our frontend. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, users will not get confused. But we have simplified a lot of things to suit vendors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let us see how you can utilize the booking module.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Pre-Requirements For Dokan WC Booking Module</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wedevs.com/dokan/\">Dokan</a> is the best multi vendor marketplace in the WordPress industry with over 30000 active installations. So, if you want to <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/246296/build-an-electronics-marketplace-with-dokan/\">build your own marketplace</a> of any niche <strong>Dokan</strong> could be the first choice. Out of the many modules, the <strong>Dokan booking</strong> module lets you create booking orders for hotel rooms, appointments, resorts, rentals, conference rooms, cars, bikes, books, party supplies, and literally, anything that can be stated as a service. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You need the following attributes to start using the Dokan WC booking plugin in full swing.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/\">WordPress</a></li><li><a href=\"https://woocommerce.com/\">WooCommerce</a></li><li><a href=\"https://wedevs.com/dokan/?utm_source=blog&utm_medium=link&utm_content=26&utm_campaign=Airbnb+alternative+site\">Dokan Light & Pro</a></li><li><a href=\"https://woocommerce.com/products/woocommerce-bookings/\">WooCommerce Bookings plugin</a>&nbsp;(Premium)</li><li><a href=\"https://wedevs.com/dokan/extensions/woocommerce-booking-integration/\">Dokan WooCommerce bookings</a>&nbsp;(Pro)</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Understanding Blocks</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"586\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2016/10/Blocks-1024x586.jpg\" alt=\"Blocks\" class=\"wp-image-279622\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/Blocks-1024x586.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/Blocks-300x172.jpg 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/Blocks-768x439.jpg 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/Blocks-1536x878.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/Blocks-45x26.jpg 45w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/Blocks-112x64.jpg 112w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/Blocks.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>To start with the Dokan WC booking module, you need to understand what a block is.  </p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p> A block is the minimum unit&nbsp;of your product&nbsp;which you are making available for booking </p></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>Booking products are time-dependent, subject to maintenance and usually do not have any <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/185907/set-up-woocommerce-shipping-on-multivendor-marketplace/\">shipping Management</a>. There are three things you need to remember about a block.</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li> <strong>Max bookings per block</strong>: This field allows you to book the product multiple times within the available time frame</li><li> <strong>Minimum booking window</strong>: It is the minimum duration of time during which a customer will have to book your next available product</li><li> <strong>Maximum booking window</strong>: The maximum range of available bookings for the product from the next available date.</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<p>So, let\'s say you want to keep an option where your customer can rent your hotel room for only half a day, and you want to rent the other half to another customer. Chunking down your booking often helps, according to the nature of your business. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Say, if you have a beach resort, most of your customers wouldn\'t want to pay for the entire day, because they only spend the evening there.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/docs/dokan-bookings-minimum-maximum.png\" alt=\"dokan-bookings-minimum-maximum\"/></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p> So, to cater to such customers, you can easily create <strong>Block</strong>. When you create a block for 3 hours with a buffer time of 30 minutes, you can sell it as many times you want. Setting a buffer time will allow you to give some time to your staff to refresh and redecorate the room for your next customer. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>That is how <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/blog/93774/dokan-bookings-brings-value-woocommerce\">this addon adds value</a> to your product.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Create Bookings with Precise&nbsp;Calendar Accuracy</h2>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>You can make your booking product available for several days only. </p></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also set days when the product will be published, but locked before the booking period actually starts. For example, you are a hotel manager and you have 3 luxury suites which you are posting online. But the holiday season starts in 3 days. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, you can easily post a booking product, with a three day no booking period and say, a one week booking time.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-002.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"930\" height=\"536\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-002.png\" alt=\"new-booking-002 Dokan WC Booking\" class=\"wp-image-80646\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-002.png 930w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-002-300x173.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-002-768x443.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-002-600x346.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 930px) 100vw, 930px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Sometimes, you can also sell your bookable products in volumes when you are targeting big. For example, you don\'t want to book your room unless someone takes it for two days. That\'s also possible.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Making Bookable Products Cost-Effective</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-003.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"914\" height=\"433\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-003.png\" alt=\"new-booking-003\" class=\"wp-image-80640\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-003.png 914w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-003-300x142.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-003-768x364.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-003-600x284.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 914px) 100vw, 914px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>We understand that charging for bookable products can be difficult and people have so many different kinds of booking requests that it gets hard for you to charge and make a profit. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>That is why, Dokan WC Booking allows you to set base costs, block costs and display costs all separately and chargeable and multipliable according to order.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Say, if you set a base cost of 100$ for your booking, and you have a block of 2 hours, then you can charge the customers for each block separately and yet get paid for the initial booking.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Making Bookings&nbsp;Person & Age Limit Specific</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Sometimes your bookable products can be age sensitive or you might even have separate arrangements for different aged customers. For example, you have separate <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/276382/create-baby-products-online-marketplace-with-dokan/\">kid-sized fun beds for children</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Related Article: <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/276382/create-baby-products-online-marketplace-with-dokan/\">How to Create a Baby Product Marketplace Online Using Dokan for Free!</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, if the customer specifically asks for any options that are related to kids or elders, you will easily be able to arrange specifically for the members. You will also be able to give better service to your customers.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-004.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"923\" height=\"772\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-004.png\" alt=\"new-booking-004 Dokan WC Booking\" class=\"wp-image-80647\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-004.png 923w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-004-300x251.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-004-768x642.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/new-booking-004-600x502.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 923px) 100vw, 923px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Add Resources to Your Booking Products</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Not only the product but also you can charge for extra resources you add to the product. That way you can easily recover any costs that you provide extra to your users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Say, you have a pool attached to one of your suite, or you have a home theater that your customers can use for family entertainment. You can charge for that with your booking product as well. For this, you need to add resources to your booking products.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2016/10/dokan-booking-vendor-dashboard.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1126\" height=\"247\" src=\"https://wedevs.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2016/10/dokan-booking-vendor-dashboard-e1475561087310.png\" alt=\"dokan-booking-vendor-dashboard Dokan WC Booking\" class=\"wp-image-80642\" srcset=\"https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/dokan-booking-vendor-dashboard-e1475561087310.png 1126w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/dokan-booking-vendor-dashboard-e1475561087310-300x66.png 300w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/dokan-booking-vendor-dashboard-e1475561087310-768x168.png 768w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/dokan-booking-vendor-dashboard-e1475561087310-1024x225.png 1024w, https://cdn.wedevs.com/uploads/2016/10/dokan-booking-vendor-dashboard-e1475561087310-600x132.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1126px) 100vw, 1126px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>We have added a completely separate menu and listing for this kind of resource.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you still have any confusion then you can give a read to this <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/docs/dokan/modules/dokan-bookings/\">document</a> to have the right ideas on how to get the benefits from this addon.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-button aligncenter\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-text-color has-very-light-gray-color has-background\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/products/plugins/dokan/woocommerce-booking-integration/\" style=\"background-color:#f2634d\"><strong>Purchase Dokan Booking Module For Just $49!</strong></a></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Final Words On Dokan WC Booking Module</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Dokan WC Booking module is one tool that allows your eCommerce vendors the freedom to create any kind of serviceable and bookable products. In this way, <a href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/133241/best-ecommerce-platforms/\">you are providing an unlimited platform</a> for sales and service agents to showcase their services and get more exposure. In hindsight, you are allowing them to get more sales, and you can earn more.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/account/80622/can-now-book-products-events-hotels-anything-new-dokan-add/\">Book Products, Events &#038; Hotels, Anything with Dokan WC Booking Module!</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wedevs.com/account\">weDevs</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1